A generic Java framework to manage bidirectional associations and inverse updates is proposed. It uses a package-private mechanism to maintain consistency between associated objects. 

Key classes A and B have the following structure:

```java
public final class A {
    private B b;
    public B getB() { return b; }
    public void setB(final B b) {
        // update b's reference, add/remove self from b's list
    }
}

public final class B {
    private final List<A> as;
    public void addA(A a) { as.add(a); }
    public void removeA(A a) { as.remove(a); }
    public List<A> getAs() { return Collections.unmodifiableList(as.stream().filter(a -> a.getB() == this).collect(Collectors.toList())); }
}
```

This framework ensures that both objects are aware of each other's existence and updates are propagated correctly.

